I"¶<p>Boids model crowd movement. Individual agents are guided through a linear combination of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/technical-indicators-are-heuristics-for-stock-market-forecasting">heuristics</a>, which results in self-organizing crowds. The heuristics are: separation (<a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/privacy-is-primarily-concerned-with-information-not-space">avoid crowded neighborhoods</a>), <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/alignment-is-reflexive-symmetric-and-transitive">alignment</a> (align with nearby agents), and cohesion (aim for the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/core-items-are-centroids-in-latent-space">centroid</a>).</p>
